THREAT: WX - A STRONG LOW PRESSURE SYSTEM IS PASSING N OF THE ISLANDS TODAY-FRIDAY. A STRONG COLD FRONT WILL PUSH DOWN THE ISLAND CHAIN THRU FRIDAY. EXPECT CONDS TO DETERIORATE TOWARDS MVFR OR LOWER THRU THE REST OF TODAY. STRONG SOUTHERLY WINDS, HEAVY RAIN AND THUNDERSTORMS ARE POSSIBLE THRU FRIDAY AFTERNOON. SEE AIRMETS FOR FORECASTED IFR, TURB, ICING. ALSO SEE SIGMET NOVEMBER SERIES.
